dcap and largecap companies for its fixed income portion the fund invests in the government and corporate securities rated within the two highest grades assigned by moodys and sp it employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis with a bottomup stock picking approach focusing on factors such as free cash flows and intelligent investment of excess cash earnings that are growing and are reasonably predictable high level of company management ownership yieldtomaturity liquidity current yield companies expected to grow shareholder value over time management teams that think and act as owners and call risk to create its portfolio the fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the sp  index barclays us governmentcredit index and lipper balanced funds index it conducts inhouse research to create its portfolio harris associates investment trust  oakmark equity and income fund was formed on november   and is domiciled in the united states detailed description  south wacker drivesuite chicago il united statesfounded in  phone  fax  key executives for harris associates investment trust  oakmark equity and income fund ms kristi lineburg rowsell cpa principal financial officer and vice president age  mr richard j gorman chief compliance officer and vice president age  mr john j kane director of global investment services age  ms vineeta d raketich vice president age  mr william carl nygren cfa partner portfolio manager and chief investment officer of us equities age  compensation as of fiscal year  harris associates investment trust  oakmark equity and income fund key developments harris associates investment trust  oakmark equity and income fund specialextraordinary shareholders meeting may   feb   harris associates investment trust  oakmark equity and income fund specialextraordinary shareholders meeting may   at  central standard time location th floor of  s wacker drive chicago il  united states similar private companies by industry company name